result.execSummary:
The defendant Dashun Dominique Williams was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Firearm-Convicted of a Felony, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dashun Dominique Williams in court with attorney Jade K Hall.  Defendant Dashun Dominique Williams in custody.  Alexandria S. Carlson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in Court for Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  

AS TO COUNT 1.  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, that a plea of guilty or no contest to the crime you are charged may result in deportation, exclusion from admission to this country, or the denial of naturalization under federal law is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Negotiations placed on the record and confirmed by the parties. Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law. 

AS TO COUNT 1.  The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 48 MONTHS, CONCURRENT to any other sentence, with credit for 110 DAYS time served, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 24 MONTHS, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 MONTHS. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
-The Court Ordered that all court costs, fees, surcharges (including the DNA and victim/witness surcharge) restitution and assessments are to be collected by DOC at MAXIMUM rate from the defendant's prison wages and any other funds and during extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment/tax intercept. 
-No new law violations. 
-Cooperate with agent. 
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-Obtain/maintain full time employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Provide DNA Sample.
-Pay supervision fees.
-Restitution set at zero.

Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
Court advised defendant appeal and of right to seek post conviction relief.
Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, ammunition, body armor, explosives and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.
Public Defender Order Appointing Counsel, Filed.

Defendant Dashun Dominique Williams in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Alexandria S. Carlson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for a scheduling conference. Defense requested a plea and sentencing date. Case adjourned to Branch 45.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for June 29, 2022 at 04:00 pm.

Defendant Dashun D Williams in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Defendant Dashun D Williams in custody.  Samantha Raygo appeared for the State of Wisconsin. PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded. Court took judicial notice of defendant's prior conviction regarding case # 06CF3841. Sworn for the State:  P.O. Steven Suvaka - MPD.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 45.  Scheduling conference scheduled for May 4, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Dashun D Williams not in court, defendant in custody.  Alexandria S. Carlson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  This matter was mistakenly placed on Br 45 calendar.  Defendant has not been appointed an attorney to date.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing.  mn  Preliminary hearing scheduled for April 6, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Dashun D Williams in court with attorney Edgar A Beltran.  Defendant Dashun D Williams in custody.  Lisa M Valenti-Jordan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Dashun D Williams appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kies, Branch 45. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for March 18, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
